title: A cute kitchen with a lot of potential for customization
text:
This little kitchen is so cute! It took about 3.5 hours to put together over the course of a few nights. It‚Äôs nice and sturdy.

Pros:
- Knobs on the stove click when you turn them. Stovetop lights up and ‚Äúsizzles‚Äù when you push the buttons on top. Batteries included.
- Ice maker on fridge makes an ice maker sound. Batteries included. Very cute.
- Lots of shelves for storage.
- Doors open and close smoothly and completely.

Cons:
- Backsplash graphics behind the sink look a little cheap.
- Shelves are the same all the way across. All the same color, even in the fridge and oven.
- There is a clothing washer, but seeing as the company makes a separate washer/dryer set (and I‚Äôve never seen a clothing washer in a kitchen) wouldn‚Äôt it make more sense for this to be a dish washer?
- The fridge / washer have a lot of vertical space, but you can‚Äôt really take advantage of it without storage containers or an avalanche of toys.
- It would be nice if there were buttons on the microwave, and weren‚Äôt just painted on.

Enhancements I made:
- Bought Melissa and Doug pots and pans set and used a command hook to attach it to the side for easy access.
- put two command hooks over the large counter top in front of the ‚Äúwindow‚Äù to hang a measuring cup set + measuring spoon set
- put some peel and stick ‚Äútile‚Äù on the backsplash for a more realistic look.
- put motion lights inside the fridge and microwave. I‚Äôll probably put two more in the freezer and oven.
- used some command hooks to put a small basket in front of the sink to hold dish rags.
- put a small basket in the sink as a dish strainer
- put some small wire organizers with legs in the fridge and washer so more items could fit in without being in boxes.

Cons:
-Because the instructions are picture and not written word it wasn't super clear to me until about halfway through that some of the screws were painted tops and others were not even though it was the same size/call letter. title: PURCHASE ELSEWHERE!!!!!
text:
With all of the other options for children‚Äôs kitchen sets out there, do not purchase this one! I am incredibly frustrated. This one was more expensive than the others, but I didn‚Äôt mind paying the money for the product advertised. Upon opening the set, the oven door was completely cracked in half. And the edges are very sharp! I called the manufacturer and was told all I needed to do was submit for a replacement part! No problem, easy enough (although my child then didn‚Äôt receive the big birthday gift as hoped). I was then told that the piece was on back order and would be a couple weeks. A month later I still haven‚Äôt heard anything, meanwhile this product is still actively being sold on Amazon. I reached out again for an ETA only to be told there is no date in sight for this part, that it probably wouldn‚Äôt be available until the summer. This set that cost almost $200 that I purchased in January. And conveniently now I am past the date of any kind of return or refund.

I understand anything can happen during shipping, but this is not right! So if you have a child who really wants this set, do not take your chances with this company! I wish I had gone elsewhere. I now have a $200 paperweight that *maybe* will be complete by summer and hopefully by then my child will still be interested in wanting this.

title: LOVE this kitchen
text:
I read many reviews on this purchase before making it. When I originally viewed this kitchen set, it was listed at one price and when I decided to purchase it, it was $35 cheaper! It is now $70 more than my purchasing price. So it may be worth watching the price on this.
I bought this for my 2 year old son for his birthday. At school, he enjoys the kitchen area and he likes to play with food outside in his play house, so this seemed like the perfect gift. We gave it to him 5 days ago and after reading reviews, we were well aware it would take 4 hours or so to put it together, and it did. Mostly because I started the process. Had my husband done the entire thing, it would have moved quicker! It is truly a QUALITY piece!! Normally things like this, the holes don't line up and we end up having to make our own holes just to get it done. But we didn't have any issues. My only complaint and just a warning... there are screws that are colored for those screws that will be visible once complete. I really really wish they had made them a different letter. I didn't realize this and in the end we had to change some screws around to make it work. So just keep that in mind... use silver anywhere it won't be visible on the outside (does not include the inside of the fridge. My son loved the stove lighting up and the sound effects and he loved all the doors that he could open and close. We have a lot of Melissa and doug Let's Play House items, and they all work well with this set. I would absolutely recommend it to anyone looking to buy a kitchen set. I chose this over the Melissa and doug set primarily for the storage component. I love the open counter, the attached fridge (what ikea's kitchen set lacked), I found it unique it had the washer but my son loves that feature too! And it is a large area for storage. I am SO happy with this purchase and I look forward to years of use!!

text:

Couple of tips for assembly:

title: Amazing kitchen, great value
text:
I shopped around for MONTHS comparing different brands and styles of play kitchens for my daughter. This set is everything I was looking. It looks realistic has all of the standard kitchen items ( sink, range, fridge, microwave). The biggest selling points for me were that it is a corner unit and all one piece. There are even built in shelves for storing the play food/dishes/ utensils. The stove burners and ice machine are battery operated and make realistic noises. The stove knobs click like a real stove turning. Extra counter space for additional appliances (we are able to fit a little Keurig, standing mixer, and toaster on the counter above the washer).

Assembly was...laborious. I‚Äôm the assembler in the house and was able to do this completely by myself, but let me tell you I had my moments. The directions are easy to follow and the parts are clearly labeled and the hardware is precisely packaged and labeled. The challenge is that there are SO MANY pieces. It took me about 5 hours total over 2 nights to complete this. I will say that the complexity of assembly really just speaks to the quality of the piece- this is not a snap together cheap plastic gaudy toy.

It looks amazing in my daughters room and she absolutely loves it. Even older cousins who are self proclaimed as ‚Äútoo old‚Äù to play with baby toys can‚Äôt help but play with this, it‚Äôs a hit!

text:
All of the previous reviews are true: it‚Äôs ridiculous to put together, the screws and bolts frequently go in backwards, and it‚Äôs great.

title: Great kitchen!
text:
Ok the set up is a pain. But I'm 31 weeks pregnant, taking care of a toddler and I did it in four hours. So it can be done! Just be aware that there are two different types of "I" screws, ones that are brown to match the wood and the others that are left silver. I didn't discover that until late in the game. But oh well. Another thing is that the back of my microwave has two round holes in it and I'm not sure why. I didn't see any other reviews with those holes.
Doesn't really matter though. Kitchen is beautiful! Love all the sounds and features. Set up with ample time before Christmas. My little man is gonna love it!

One year update....
Kitchen has held up great! Except the water knobs fell off. I'm actually really happy I bought this piece in particular. My plan was for the kids to share a room so that our spare room could still function as a play room. That didn't work out. So I had this seemingly huge kitchen I had to fit in the corner of my son's room. Not only did it fit perfectly BUT it also stores a ton of toys! It's really like a 2 for 1. Toy storage plus it's a toy! Love it!

text: Ordered this as a Christmas gift for my 3 year old granddaughter who is obsessed with helping out in the kitchen, and it didn't disappoint! It ships unassembled in a single box, so it weighs a ton, and it does take a bit of time and attention to detail to put it together. Details like the light up water dispenser on the fridge door, the burners that flicker and make boiling sounds, and the pretty curtain in the laundry window. The materials felt sturdy and fit together perfectly, and the cabinets can store all of her food play items easily. It also looks like it's going to be easy for us adults to keep clean, too; the surfaces look and feel like they'll be very scrubbable without damaging the surfaces. I will DEFINITELY be buying from this seller/manufacturer again, and letting my friends know how pleased I am with my order- and so is my granddaughter!

When attempting to gently, yes I said gently, slide the counter on where the kitchen sink is supposed to go, one of the side pieces completely snapped in half and we had to use wood glue to fix it. Now that we have built this and taken it apart and built this back up we now realize we don't even have enough screws to complete this kitchen. I am livid. title: Big Hit
text:
First and foremost this kitchen is a HUGE hit with every child that has encountered it. The children at my daughter's birthday descended on this thing like a band of wild hyenas. Thanks to it's design it was easy (if not choatic) for all 6 children to play with this thing at once. They love going around the back to play through the windows and there are many doors to open and buttons to press. We also added some stick on LED lights, which added to the fun.

As an additional note...
I have assembled every stick of furniture in my home, including those with no verbal or only non English directions, and this was by far the most tedious build I've ever done. Please take note there are multiple parts (screws) with the same identifying letter with different colored tops (brown for visible parts on the dark surface when completed and then silver. Strongly recommend taking a good look at your hardware and where the screw might be seen from when assembled.

title: Awesome!
text:
This kitchen is amazing! The wood, the sturdiness, all amazing! I will agree with everyone else, the assembly was a NIGHTMARE! I'll disagree with others when they say "don't use a drill" There's NO WAY we could have gotten this put together without a drill! Just don't push down super hard is all. But some of the screws we couldn't put in with just a screwdriver. The smal drill helped SO MUCH.
The instructions were SUPER HARD to follow on some things! Words would help greatly!! We mixed up two of the first three pieces when we started actually assembling it. We got 3/4 of the way finished when this mistake was noticed.... it was where the backboard goes for the window. There was no "oh lets unscrew a couple of screws and swap them around" oh no!! We had to undo the WHOLE thing!! Granted we put it together faster the second time around but dang it was crazy to have to undo all of it!
Just know when you start putting this together, the first three pieces, make sure the grooved in piece is on the bottom part of the kitchen, not in the middle and you'll avoid this mistake.
I do wish there was a little more countertop or storage space but overall this kitchen is amazing and my grand children love it! <3 Even the adults love it! lol

title: Purchased this for my 2 year old son for Christmas ...
text:
Purchased this for my 2 year old son for Christmas. Here are 6 important things you should do/know first:
(1) Open box and layout each piece in numerical order and follow the instructions, step by step except for my below #2 and #5.
(2) Pull the plastic tabs that separate the batteries from the connectors on the ice cube maker and both gas range burners before attaching them
(3) There are duplicate screws with natural silver metal heads and DTM (dyed to match) brown metal heads. Instructions do not advise when to use which and I still don't know. I would advise to use all the silver ones first and once you've go through those, start using the brown ones.
(4) Make sure to use the Brown side of the bottom corner back board to face the front (towards you). The white side should face the back.
(5) Install the Faucet before installing the counter top (as you would in real life)
(6) There is 1 wooden dowel. Keep this. It's for the curtains.

It took 2 people 3.5 hours to assemble the entire project. Once it was done, it was well worth it. My son loves it and I added a battery operated light switch for above the counter top and in the oven. I also printed a picture of our family with our phone numbers and double-side taped it onto the phone. And to prevent items from falling behind the kitchen from the counter tops, I printed an outdoor scenery and taped that on cardboard to cover the openings. There's a lot more you can add to this to make it more authentic and personalize it.

The doors can be a little hard to open and close as the locking mechanism is a little tight but should loosen over time, or at least your child will get stronger. The kitchen could use a another shelf in the fridge and dishwasher.

Otherwise, my son absolutely loves the ice cube maker and faux gas flames and sounds. My next project is to turn it into a real working faucet.

title: When I spend hundreds of dollars, I expect a product to work
text:
I bought this kitchen for my daughter this past Christmas and while I will say that it is a beautiful toy, I don't think it's worth the hassle!

I'm entirely competent, I build all of our real furniture, all of my daughter's toys. I have never come across a product with worse instructions. Not only were they extremely unclear and difficult to follow, but some steps were missing entirely! I had all kinds of unused parts at the end and combed back through the manual searching for what to do with them... only to find they were never mentioned. So after spending about 4 hours building this thing as per the instructions, I had to spend another 2 hours taking apart large portions of it to add parts that apparently they forgot existed! But a frustrating building experience is almost a right of passage for parents, no?

Well, the issues don't end there. One of the stove burners doesn't work. It worked intermittently a handful of times while I tried fixing it, before dying completely. When I went to their site to order a replacement part, I was prompted to provide what I can only describe as an annoying and inconvenient amount of information. I know that's a small thing to fuss over, but given how needlessly frustrating every aspect of this kitchen had been up until that point, proving several different types of proof of purchase made me mad. It just felt like they were doing whatever they could to avoid actually having to replace anything. And of course when I go to pick the part I needed, the site informed me that they no longer made that part and it was not available to order. No further instructions on how to remedy the situation, basically just "sorry, we don't make and don't have the product you bought a month ago". Which is ridiculous. Again, the impression I got is that KidKraft is doing everything in its power to not replace parts that THEY made poorly. Not parts that had broken with a lot of play and use, parts that arrived broken.

So now I am in the process of emailing KidKraft about the part, but again the process is drawn out and frustrating. And as the window on their 90 day guarantee is quickly closing, I thought I might have better luck leaving a review here than I have from emailing them directly.

Look, if the product were cheap, all this might be acceptable. However, it's not! For the money I spent on this headache of a play kitchen, I could have made under our tree look like we robbed Santa's workshop. I would certainly think twice about purchasing anything from KidKraft in the future because of this experience.

EDIT Feb 16:
They finally sent a replacement part which arrived in the mail today. It was the wrong part. The saga continues.

text: I spent a year searching for a good play kitchen for my two and a half year old for Christmas this year because I knew I needed something for her that she can both play with for a long time and was sturdy. I won't lie, it took me 6 hours to assemble it. I am a single parent, so I had no help which was fine. The only problem I have with it is that there were about 10 points where the screws did not match up with the already drilled inserts, so there are some misalignment issues. However, it is very cute and I'm so excited for the years to come and the laughter and play about to tenfold in my house! I am pleased with how compact it is, because my home is less than 500 square feet so it fits perfectly in the play corner! My daughter's review is "it's so pretty mom! So pretty! I'm cooking! You hungry? I'm making dinner!" I would definitely recommend as long as you have a good amount of time and patience to assemble.

title: Easy Assembly ‚Äî 5 hours or less

My original intention was to hire someone to put it together. But I decided to give it a try myself and found it very easy to assemble. One note: some screwheads are brown and some are silver. title: High quality play kitchen for a great price!
text:
We would highly recommend this play kitchen! As some reviews have already stated, the assembly required to get it together is significant. My husband, who is pretty handy, took about four hours to put it all together the night before we opened gifts.

The quality of the product is great! There were a few scratches on two or three of the pieces when we unboxed it. It was a minor disappointment in the grand scheme of the things. None of the scratches were on prominent pieces, so it didn't detract from the look of the kitchen at all.

We added puck lights per the suggestion of another review. I would highly recommend this addition. We happened to get lights that have the ability for multiple colors so we could have a red light for the oven, a blue light for the fridge and freezer and white light for the microwave and under cabinet lighting.

Since receiving her gift, our 2.5 year old daughter has played with it constantly. We are hopeful it will provide a lot of entertainment for her in the years to come!

title: Sturdy, easy to build, super cute!
text:
Aside from being super cute, it was also the perfect gift for my 2 year old. She LOVES it! It‚Äôs sturdy and was fairly easy to put together - proud to say this mama did it without the help of my hubby (I‚Äôm hard headed).

It seems overwhelming at first, but if you have a drill and can follow instructions... you‚Äôll do JUST fine. I suggest using the drill over a screwdriver, and laying all of your kitchen pieces out in groups/numbers (create piles - each piece of wood has a number on it), and only open the screw packs you need as you go along.

It does take a few hours to put it together. I did it over a course of a few days. Days 1 & 2, I spent approximately 45 min to an hour on it. The 3rd day took ~30 min. Not sure I have the patience to do it all on one day.

Overall, great purchase. Perfect size, super cute... my toddler spends endless hours of fun cooking for her dolls. :)

title: Worth it.

[[VIDEOID:76c9ce2d2f4226207f2523556aa18357]] Put this together by myself in about 3 1/2 hrs. I needed a second set of hands twice because the parts I was assembling were too long to hold both ends myself in order to connect them.

Some of the screws were painted so it matches the wood color and I wound up mixing them up with the ones that were not supposed to be visible. If you‚Äôre handy, that probably would be caught early. Another thing is that a few times, there wasn‚Äôt enough hand space to screw in all the way, so it takes extra time to screw in using Less than 1/4 turns.

One thing I noted is that when the batteries need to be replaced for the stove and fridge, it‚Äôll pretty much be a pain because of the award angle you‚Äôll have to unscrew them to change the batteries...for the stove at least.

It doesn‚Äôt come with accessories, so I ordered separate stuff to come at the same time. It would have been nice to have lights above the sink and in the fridge along with the sounds the kitchen makes, but I I‚Äôll purchase some and stick them on.

My kids, 2&3 love this kitchen and it seems sturdy enough to last some time. Very satisfied overall with the purchase.

It may save some aggravation to cut the package the screws come in and separate them while they‚Äôre still in the package for easier identification of parts.

title: Grab some wine before assembling!
text: My son had been begging me for this exact play kitchen for months and when Amazon had a used one for sale I just had to get it. I've never bought anything used on Amazon before so I was a little concerned. But it arrived on time. I was warned that the box would be damaged and that some parts were cosmetically damaged but that it worked and had all the parts. I was okay with that risk and proceeded anyway. When we got it the box was so destroyed that I was surprised that it even made it to my house. Assembly was an absolute nightmare, it took probably 3 hours to do by myself and with a drill. You don't need it but it helps. But be careful a drill can be too powerful for some parts so you'll need a regular screwdriver as well. We've had a different kid kraft kitchen before and even though it was small, assembly for that was horrid as well. So I was expecting as much. There were several parts missing despite the fact that the description said the damages were only cosmetic and that it would be fully functional. Well, it's not functional with missing parts. So that was extremely disappointing. However, I was able to order the exact parts for it from the kidkraft website for free and that was honestly so amazing and for that alone I was impressed with kidkraft. We added some stick on lights for a more homey feel. In my honest opinion I am satisfied with the finished product. HOWEVER, I do not recommend buying this at full price as it doesn't seem worth it in my opinion.

title: Before you put together look at the head of the screws

title: BEST KIDS KITCHEN OUT THERE!
text:
Amazing! I'm one of those moms who researches a big toy for months before I purchase. I became that way after I bought a few toys and after I received I wasn't happy.

Needless to say I tried several kitchens before and this by FAR is the best! The sounds from the burners and ice maker are very realist and the extra counter space and washing machine just put this over the top. It's the tallest kitchen I could find and enough space for a few kids to play with at the same time.

I posted pictures of my little girl playing with it! I'm also posting videos on YouTube. She loves that it actually has room to fit her cookies and cakes into the oven and microwave. The Melissa and Doug Disney cookies fit in the oven perfectly! (The bigger cookie sheet if their Christmas and regular cookies does not fit). Her previous kitchens microwaves and oven could hold a plate much less and cookie sheet.

My only disappointment is not enough shelves in fridge and bottom cabinet.

Still the best out there and the quality is over the top! It's heavy and not going to fall over on your one year old like my previous step 2 kitchen did. I put this together myself super easy just a little time consuming.

If this was helpful please give it a thumbs up!

The water/ice slot is way too small for any cup except a Dixie cup, like other reviews also state.

There is no backing to the fridge so things fall out the back. I realize it should probably be up against a wall, but it‚Äôd be more convenient if it also had backing like the oven.

Overall, mostly happy with it since the kids love it and it is being used like we‚Äôd intended. However, would consider buying a different brand that has those conveniences if I had it to do over again.
